Note: Java Semantic Analyzer for Translation Translation System
Note: Handles type checking, scope analysis, inheritance, generics, annotations
Note: Supports Java 8+ features including lambdas, method references, streams

Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/lexer.runa" as Lexer
@Reasoning:
Top-level analyzer context. Carries a stacked symbol table, the active
scope pointer, a class-hierarchy map for inheritance lookups, a separate
generic-constraints map (bounds, variances), the annotation table for
post-resolution metadata, accumulating error/warning lists, an imports
list, and pointers tracking the class/method currently under analysis so
nested AST nodes can resolve enclosing context. lambda_contexts is a stack
because lambdas can be nested and each carries its own capture set and
target functional interface.
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaSemanticAnalyzer":
    symbol_table as Integer  Note: Map of scopes and symbols
    current_scope as Integer  Note: Current scope context
    class_hierarchy as Integer  Note: Map of class inheritance relationships
    generic_constraints as Integer  Note: Map of generic type constraints
    annotation_table as Integer  Note: Map of annotations and their metadata
    error_list as Integer  Note: List of semantic errors
    warning_list as Integer  Note: List of semantic warnings
    imports as Integer  Note: List of imported packages and classes
    current_class as Integer  Note: Currently analyzed class context
    current_method as Integer  Note: Currently analyzed method context
    lambda_contexts as Integer  Note: Stack of lambda expression contexts
End Type

@Reasoning:
Lexical scope record. scope_type identifies the kind (class/method/block/
lambda) so resolution rules can vary (e.g., 'this' resolves at class scope
but is captured at lambda scope). parent_scope chains to the enclosing
scope. access_level tracks the default visibility for entries declared
here (matters for class bodies). is_static flags static contexts where
'this' is unavailable.
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaScope":
    scope_type as String  Note: "class", "method", "block", "lambda"
    parent_scope as Integer  Note: Reference to parent scope
    symbols as Integer  Note: Map of symbol names to symbol info
    access_level as String  Note: "public", "private", "protected", "package"
    is_static as Integer  Note: 1 if static context, 0 otherwise
End Type

@Reasoning:
Symbol-table entry covering classes, methods, fields, locals, and
parameters. Carries the resolved Java type as a string for now (replaced by
proper JavaType references after first-pass resolution), modifier set,
annotations, generic parameters (for declarations) or type arguments (for
uses), an initialized flag for definite-assignment checking, and source
position for diagnostics.
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaSymbol":
    name as String
    symbol_type as String  Note: "class", "method", "field", "variable", "parameter"
    data_type as String  Note: Java type (String, int, List<String>, etc.)
    modifiers as Integer  Note: List of modifiers (public, static, final, etc.)
    scope as Integer  Note: Reference to containing scope
    annotations as Integer  Note: List of annotations
    generic_parameters as Integer  Note: List of generic type parameters
    is_initialized as Integer  Note: 1 if initialized, 0 otherwise
    line_number as Integer
    column_number as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Resolved Java type. Separates the base name from generic arguments and
array dimensions so type compatibility can be checked structurally.
is_primitive disables boxing-and-null behavior for the eight primitive
types. is_nullable is set per-use (e.g., @Nullable annotation) — primitives
are never nullable. package_name disambiguates same-name classes across
packages (java.util.List vs java.awt.List).
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaType":
    base_type as String  Note: "int", "String", "List", etc.
    generic_arguments as Integer  Note: List of generic type arguments
    array_dimensions as Integer  Note: Number of array dimensions
    is_primitive as Integer  Note: 1 if primitive type, 0 otherwise
    is_nullable as Integer  Note: 1 if can be null, 0 otherwise
    package_name as String  Note: Package of the type
End Type

@Reasoning:
Method signature record used for overload resolution and override
checking. parameter_types is ordered (positional matching); throws_clauses
is unordered (checked-exception propagation rules don't depend on ordering).
generic_parameters here describes method-level type parameters (e.g.,
<T> T identity(T x)).
@End Reasoning
Type called "JavaMethodSignature":
    name as String
    parameter_types as Integer  Note: List of parameter types
    return_type as String
    modifiers as Integer  Note: List of modifiers
    generic_parameters as Integer  Note: List of generic type parameters
    throws_clauses as Integer  Note: List of exception types
End Type

@Reasoning:
Constructs the analyzer with empty tables, lists, and a "global" scope
already installed and set as current. Pre-populating the global scope means
subsequent class declarations always have a parent_scope to chain to —
removing a null check from the hot path.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_java_semantic_analyzer" returns Integer:
    Note: Create new Java semantic analyzer instance

    Let analyzer be a value of type JavaSemanticAnalyzer with
        symbol_table as proc create_dict,
        current_scope as 0,
        class_hierarchy as proc create_dict,
        generic_constraints as proc create_dict,
        annotation_table as proc create_dict,
        error_list as proc create_list,
        warning_list as proc create_list,
        imports as proc create_list,
        current_class as 0,
        current_method as 0,
        lambda_contexts as proc create_stack

    Note: Initialize global scope
    Let global_scope be a value of type JavaScope with
        scope_type as "global",
        parent_scope as 0,
        symbols as proc create_dict,
        access_level as "public",
        is_static as 0

    proc set_dict_value with analyzer.symbol_table, "global", global_scope
    Set analyzer.current_scope to global_scope

    Return analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Visitor dispatch keyed on the AST node tag. Match cascade delegates to
specialized analyzers for declarations, control-flow, and expression forms.
The fall-through (Otherwise) recurses into children, so unknown or
container-only nodes propagate analysis without explicit handlers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_java_ast" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Perform complete semantic analysis of Java AST

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    Match node_type:
        When AST_COMPILATION_UNIT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_compilation_unit with analyzer, ast
        When AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_class_declaration with analyzer, ast
        When AST_METHOD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_method_declaration with analyzer, ast
        When AST_FIELD_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_field_declaration with analyzer, ast
        When AST_VARIABLE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_variable_declaration with analyzer, ast
        When AST_BLOCK from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_block with analyzer, ast
        When AST_IF_STATEMENT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_if_statement with analyzer, ast
        When AST_FOR_STATEMENT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_for_statement with analyzer, ast
        When AST_WHILE_STATEMENT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_while_statement with analyzer, ast
        When AST_TRY_STATEMENT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_try_statement with analyzer, ast
        When AST_LAMBDA_EXPRESSION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_lambda_expression with analyzer, ast
        When AST_METHOD_CALL from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_method_call with analyzer, ast
        When AST_FIELD_ACCESS from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_field_access with analyzer, ast
        When AST_ASSIGNMENT from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_assignment with analyzer, ast
        When AST_BINARY_OPERATION from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_binary_operation with analyzer, ast
        When AST_IDENTIFIER from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_identifier with analyzer, ast
        When AST_LITERAL from Parser:
            Return proc analyze_literal with analyzer, ast
        Otherwise:
            Return proc analyze_children with analyzer, ast
    End Match
End Process

@Reasoning:
Three-pass walk over compilation-unit children: imports first (so type
references can resolve), then package declaration (sets context for
unqualified names), then type declarations. The order is deliberate
because later passes depend on the lookup tables populated by earlier
ones.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_compilation_unit" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java compilation unit (source file)

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 32
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 40

    Note: Process imports first
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Let child_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_IMPORT_DECLARATION from Parser:
            proc analyze_import_declaration with analyzer, child
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Process package declaration
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_PACKAGE_DECLARATION from Parser:
            proc analyze_package_declaration with analyzer, child
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Note: Process type declarations (classes, interfaces, enums)
    Set index to 0
    While index is less than child_count:
        Set child to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
        Set child_type to proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with child, 0

        If child_type is equal to AST_CLASS_DECLARATION from Parser or
           child_type is equal to AST_INTERFACE_DECLARATION from Parser or
           child_type is equal to AST_ENUM_DECLARATION from Parser:
            proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, child
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Creates a class symbol, registers it in the enclosing scope, pushes a new
class scope, records inheritance and interface implements in the hierarchy
map, recurses into the body, then validates abstract/non-abstract
completeness. The save/restore of current_scope and current_class makes
nested classes work correctly because both fields are stacked locally.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_class_declaration" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java class declaration with inheritance and generics

    Let class_name be proc get_ast_name from ast
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_modifiers from ast

    Note: Create class symbol
    Let class_symbol be a value of type JavaSymbol with
        name as class_name,
        symbol_type as "class",
        data_type as class_name,
        modifiers as modifiers,
        scope as analyzer.current_scope,
        annotations as proc get_ast_annotations with ast,
        generic_parameters as proc get_ast_generic_parameters with ast,
        is_initialized as 1,
        line_number as proc get_ast_line with ast,
        column_number as proc get_ast_column from ast

    Note: Add class to current scope
    proc add_symbol_to_scope with analyzer.current_scope, class_name, class_symbol

    Note: Create class scope
    Let class_scope be a value of type JavaScope with
        scope_type as "class",
        parent_scope as analyzer.current_scope,
        symbols as proc create_dict,
        access_level as proc get_access_level with modifiers,
        is_static as proc has_modifier with modifiers, "static"

    Note: Push class scope
    Let previous_scope be analyzer.current_scope
    Let previous_class be analyzer.current_class
    Set analyzer.current_scope to class_scope
    Set analyzer.current_class to class_symbol

    Note: Process inheritance
    Let extends_clause be proc get_ast_extends_clause from ast
    If extends_clause is not equal to 0:
        Let superclass_name be proc get_type_name from extends_clause
        proc add_inheritance_relationship with analyzer.class_hierarchy, class_name, superclass_name
        proc check_inheritance_validity with analyzer, class_name, superclass_name, ast
    End If

    Note: Process interface implementations
    Let implements_clause be proc get_ast_implements_clause from ast
    If implements_clause is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_interface_implementations with analyzer, class_name, implements_clause, ast
    End If

    Note: Analyze class body
    Let body be proc get_ast_body from ast
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, body
    End If

    Note: Validate class completeness
    proc validate_class_completeness with analyzer, class_symbol, ast

    Note: Restore previous scope
    Set analyzer.current_scope to previous_scope
    Set analyzer.current_class to previous_class

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds a method signature (used for overload-conflict detection within
the class), creates a method symbol, pushes a method scope, analyzes
parameters into that scope, recurses into the body, and validates return
statement compatibility against the declared return type. Constructor
forms (no return type) and abstract forms (no body) are handled by skipping
respective sections when the relevant AST piece is null.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_method_declaration" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java method declaration with overloading and generics

    Let method_name be proc get_ast_name from ast
    Let return_type be proc get_ast_return_type from ast
    Let parameters be proc get_ast_parameters from ast
    Let modifiers be proc get_ast_modifiers from ast

    Note: Create method signature
    Let signature be a value of type JavaMethodSignature with
        name as method_name,
        parameter_types as proc extract_parameter_types with parameters,
        return_type as return_type,
        modifiers as modifiers,
        generic_parameters as proc get_ast_generic_parameters with ast,
        throws_clauses as proc get_ast_throws_clauses from ast

    Note: Check for method overloading conflicts
    proc check_method_overloading with analyzer, signature, ast

    Note: Create method symbol
    Let method_symbol be a value of type JavaSymbol with
        name as method_name,
        symbol_type as "method",
        data_type as return_type,
        modifiers as modifiers,
        scope as analyzer.current_scope,
        annotations as proc get_ast_annotations with ast,
        generic_parameters as signature.generic_parameters,
        is_initialized as 1,
        line_number as proc get_ast_line with ast,
        column_number as proc get_ast_column from ast

    Note: Add method to current scope
    proc add_symbol_to_scope with analyzer.current_scope, method_name, method_symbol

    Note: Create method scope
    Let method_scope be a value of type JavaScope with
        scope_type as "method",
        parent_scope as analyzer.current_scope,
        symbols as proc create_dict,
        access_level as proc get_access_level with modifiers,
        is_static as proc has_modifier with modifiers, "static"

    Note: Push method scope
    Let previous_scope be analyzer.current_scope
    Let previous_method be analyzer.current_method
    Set analyzer.current_scope to method_scope
    Set analyzer.current_method to method_symbol

    Note: Analyze parameters
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_method_parameters with analyzer, parameters, ast
    End If

    Note: Analyze method body
    Let body be proc get_ast_body from ast
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, body

        Note: Check return statements match return type
        proc validate_return_statements with analyzer, method_symbol, body, ast
    End If

    Note: Validate method constraints
    proc validate_method_constraints with analyzer, method_symbol, ast

    Note: Restore previous scope
    Set analyzer.current_scope to previous_scope
    Set analyzer.current_method to previous_method

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pushes a lambda scope (so 'this' resolves to the enclosing class, not the
lambda itself), runs analysis on parameters and body, then performs closure
analysis to record effectively-final captures and infers the lambda's
target functional-interface type. The inferred type is attached to the AST
node so the translator can emit a correct anonymous-class equivalent or
preserve the lambda form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_lambda_expression" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java lambda expression with type inference and closure

    Let parameters be proc get_ast_parameters from ast
    Let body be proc get_ast_body from ast

    Note: Create lambda scope
    Let lambda_scope be a value of type JavaScope with
        scope_type as "lambda",
        parent_scope as analyzer.current_scope,
        symbols as proc create_dict,
        access_level as "private",
        is_static as 0

    Note: Push lambda context
    proc push_lambda_context with analyzer.lambda_contexts, lambda_scope
    Let previous_scope be analyzer.current_scope
    Set analyzer.current_scope to lambda_scope

    Note: Analyze lambda parameters with type inference
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_lambda_parameters with analyzer, parameters, ast
    End If

    Note: Analyze lambda body
    proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, body

    Note: Perform closure analysis
    proc analyze_closure_variables with analyzer, lambda_scope, ast

    Note: Infer functional interface type
    Let functional_interface be proc infer_functional_interface_type with analyzer, ast
    proc set_ast_inferred_type with ast, functional_interface

    Note: Restore previous scope
    Set analyzer.current_scope to previous_scope
    proc pop_lambda_context with analyzer.lambda_contexts

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a method call: analyzes the receiver (or falls back to the
current class for implicit-this calls), collects argument types, then runs
overload resolution. On failure adds an error and returns 0 to halt
propagation; on success records the inferred return type on the call node
and checks access modifiers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_method_call" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java method call with overload resolution and generics

    Let method_name be proc get_ast_method_name from ast
    Let receiver be proc get_ast_receiver from ast
    Let arguments be proc get_ast_arguments from ast

    Note: Analyze receiver expression
    Let receiver_type be ""
    If receiver is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, receiver
        Set receiver_type to proc get_ast_inferred_type from receiver
    Otherwise:
        Note: Method call on current class or static import
        Set receiver_type to proc get_current_class_type from analyzer
    End If

    Note: Analyze arguments
    Let argument_types be proc create_list
    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        Let arg_count be proc get_list_size from arguments
        Let arg_index be 0
        While arg_index is less than arg_count:
            Let argument be proc get_list_item with arguments, arg_index
            proc analyze_java_ast with analyzer, argument
            Let arg_type be proc get_ast_inferred_type from argument
            proc add_to_list with argument_types, arg_type
            Set arg_index to arg_index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Resolve method overloading
    Let resolved_method be proc resolve_method_overloading with analyzer, receiver_type, method_name, argument_types, ast

    If resolved_method is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Cannot resolve method", ast
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check access permissions
    proc check_method_access with analyzer, resolved_method, ast

    Note: Set inferred return type
    Let return_type be proc get_method_return_type from resolved_method
    proc set_ast_inferred_type with ast, return_type

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Layered compatibility check following JLS assignment-context rules: exact
match, primitive widening (byte->short->int->long->float->double),
subtype (class hierarchy), interface implementation, generic compatibility
(parameterized type subtyping), and autoboxing/unboxing. Each layer is
short-circuit — first to match returns 1.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_type_compatibility" takes analyzer as Integer, expected_type as String, actual_type as String, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if actual type is compatible with expected type

    Note: Handle exact match
    If expected_type is equal to actual_type:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Handle primitive widening conversions
    If proc is_primitive_widening_conversion with expected_type, actual_type is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Handle inheritance relationships
    If proc is_subtype with analyzer.class_hierarchy, actual_type, expected_type is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Handle interface implementations
    If proc implements_interface with analyzer.class_hierarchy, actual_type, expected_type is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Handle generic type compatibility
    If proc is_generic_type_compatible with expected_type, actual_type is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Handle autoboxing/unboxing
    If proc is_autoboxing_compatible with expected_type, actual_type is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Implements JLS 15.12.2 overload resolution in five phases: exact match,
widening primitive conversion, autoboxing/unboxing, widening reference
conversion, and finally varargs. Each phase narrows the candidate set; the
first phase yielding exactly one match wins. Multiple matches in the final
phase are reported as ambiguous.
@End Reasoning
@Performance_Hints:
O(c * p) where c is candidate count and p is parameter count, dominated
by the filtering passes. Candidates are pre-fetched once via
find_candidate_methods.
@End Performance_Hints
Process called "resolve_method_overloading" takes analyzer as Integer, receiver_type as String, method_name as String, argument_types as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve method overloading using Java's method resolution rules

    Note: Find all candidate methods
    Let candidates be proc find_candidate_methods with analyzer, receiver_type, method_name

    If proc get_list_size with candidates is equal to 0:
        Return 0  Note: No methods found
    End If

    Note: Phase 1: Exact match (no conversion)
    Let exact_matches be proc filter_exact_matches with candidates, argument_types
    If proc get_list_size with exact_matches is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_list_item with exact_matches, 0
    End If

    Note: Phase 2: Widening primitive conversions
    Let widening_matches be proc filter_widening_matches with candidates, argument_types
    If proc get_list_size with widening_matches is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_list_item with widening_matches, 0
    End If

    Note: Phase 3: Autoboxing/unboxing
    Let boxing_matches be proc filter_boxing_matches with candidates, argument_types
    If proc get_list_size with boxing_matches is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_list_item with boxing_matches, 0
    End If

    Note: Phase 4: Widening reference conversions
    Let reference_matches be proc filter_reference_matches with analyzer, candidates, argument_types
    If proc get_list_size with reference_matches is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_list_item with reference_matches, 0
    End If

    Note: Phase 5: Variable arity (varargs)
    Let vararg_matches be proc filter_vararg_matches with candidates, argument_types
    If proc get_list_size with vararg_matches is equal to 1:
        Return proc get_list_item with vararg_matches, 0
    End If

    Note: If multiple matches remain, it's ambiguous
    If proc get_list_size with candidates is greater than 1:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Ambiguous method call", ast
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Looks up declared type-parameter bounds for type_name and validates that
each supplied generic argument satisfies the corresponding constraint.
Arity mismatch is rejected before the per-argument check so we don't
mis-pair bounds with arguments.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_generic_constraints" takes analyzer as Integer, type_name as String, generic_args as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate generic type constraints and bounds

    Let type_constraints be proc get_dict_value with analyzer.generic_constraints, type_name
    If type_constraints is equal to 0:
        Return 1  Note: No constraints to validate
    End If

    Let arg_count be proc get_list_size from generic_args
    Let constraint_count be proc get_list_size from type_constraints

    If arg_count is not equal to constraint_count:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Generic argument count mismatch", ast
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Validate each type argument against its constraint
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than arg_count:
        Let type_arg be proc get_list_item with generic_args, index
        Let constraint be proc get_list_item with type_constraints, index

        If proc satisfies_constraint with analyzer, type_arg, constraint is equal to 0:
            proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "Type argument violates constraint", ast
            Return 0
        End If

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates a single annotation usage. Unknown annotation names produce a
warning (not an error) since user-defined annotations are common and may be
declared elsewhere. Parameter validation enforces declared element types
and required defaults; target validation checks that the annotation may
appear on the annotated element kind (class, method, field, etc.).
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_annotation" takes analyzer as Integer, annotation as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze Java annotation usage and validate parameters

    Let annotation_name be proc get_ast_name from annotation
    Let parameters be proc get_ast_annotation_parameters from annotation

    Note: Check if annotation is known
    Let annotation_info be proc get_dict_value with analyzer.annotation_table, annotation_name
    If annotation_info is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "Unknown annotation", annotation
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Validate annotation parameters
    If parameters is not equal to 0:
        proc validate_annotation_parameters with analyzer, annotation_info, parameters, annotation
    End If

    Note: Check annotation target validity
    proc validate_annotation_target with analyzer, annotation_info, annotation

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor returning the accumulated error list. Callers iterate this after
the analysis pass to surface diagnostics or abort translation if non-empty.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_semantic_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return list of semantic errors found during analysis
    Return analyzer.error_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accessor returning the accumulated warning list — separated from errors so
translation can proceed in the presence of warnings but halt on errors.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_semantic_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return list of semantic warnings found during analysis
    Return analyzer.warning_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic error with the message and source coordinates pulled
from the AST node. Errors are accumulated rather than thrown so analysis
can continue and report multiple problems per run.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_semantic_error" takes analyzer as Integer, message as String, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add semantic error with location information

    Let error be a value of type Dictionary[String, Any] with
        "message" as message,
        "line" as proc get_ast_line with ast,
        "column" as proc get_ast_column with ast,
        "file" as proc get_ast_file with ast,
        "severity" as "error"

    proc add_to_list with analyzer.error_list, error
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic warning. Identical structure to add_semantic_error but
into the warning_list — keeps the two streams separable for downstream
gating decisions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_semantic_warning" takes analyzer as Integer, message as String, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add semantic warning with location information

    Let warning be a value of type Dictionary[String, Any] with
        "message" as message,
        "line" as proc get_ast_line with ast,
        "column" as proc get_ast_column with ast,
        "file" as proc get_ast_file with ast,
        "severity" as "warning"

    proc add_to_list with analyzer.warning_list, warning
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Helper processes for symbol table management, type checking, and scope analysis

@Reasoning:
Allocates the backing storage for a hash-table-style symbol dictionary
(24-byte header). The header layout is decoded by other helpers; this
keeps allocation behind a single name so future representation changes
don't ripple across the analyzer.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_dict" returns Integer:
    Note: Create dictionary for symbol storage
